		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I'm not sure if two resistors and two diodes are enough to prevent stray writes as the CPU begins to lose power. I seem to remember Super NES games being engineered not to require the player to hold reset while turning power off.</div><br /><br />Vcc has to be greater than Vbattery for SRAM's /CE to be enabled by the MAD-1, so maybe this is enough to prevent issues during power down.<br /><br />The carts do prevent issues during power up by connecting CE to /RESET on most MAD boards from what I understand.

		

